1.   A particular neighborhood, place, or district:  "Localities, even individual villages, developed their own languages"   (Wall Street Journal). 2.   The fact or quality of having position in space. 1.  a neighbourhood or area 2.  the site or scene of an event 3.  the fact or condition of having a location or position in space    1.   a specific place or area; location:   They moved to another locality.      2.   the state or fact of having a location:   the locality that every material object must have.  